Former Governor of Abia State and Chief Whip of the senate, Dr. Orji Kalu, has felicitated with his erstwhile political adviser and former Minister of Labour and Productivity, Chief Emeka Wogu on the occasion of his 56th birthday anniversary.
Describing Wogu as hardworking, gentle and urbane, Kalu joined other Abians in celebrating the accomplishments of the celebrant in all spheres of life.
While admonishing the former Minister to sustain his goodworks,  the Senate Chief Whip prayed to God to grant the celebrator longer life in the service of humanity.
In a goodwill message, Kalu said:”On behalf of the people of Abia North Senatorial District, I wholeheartedly congratulate my former Political Adviser and former Minister of Labour and Productivity, Chief Emeka Wogu as he clocks 56. The contributions of the former minster to the growth and development of Abia state and Nigeria in general are remarkable and worthy of commendation. As the celebrator marks his birthday, I encourage him to sustain his good deeds.”The former governor wished the former minister continued success in life. Click Here>>>>>>Anti-kidnap and anti-theft device for tracking and listening<<<<<< 